ChatGPT said:
Given the new information, the correct operational loss event category is:

âœ… Internal Fraud

Why:

The collections employee intentionally orchestrated the robbery

The miscreants were accomplices, not external criminals

This involves misappropriation of assets and intentional misconduct by an employee

Under Basel operational risk event types, this clearly falls under Internal Fraud, not External Fraud or Theft.


